ZH: 我只能在五点之前回家，因为有时间限制。
EN: I can only go home before 5 PM because there is a time constraint.

ZH: 这个商店每人限购两件商品。
EN: This store has a limit of two items per person.

ZH: 我收到了会议的邀请，但是时间地点限制了我是否能参加。
EN: I received an invitation to the meeting, but the time and location restrict whether I can attend.

ZH: 请确保你的食物摄入量限制在一定范围内。
EN: Please make sure your food intake is limited within a certain range.

ZH: 他的身体健康状况限制了他的行动能力。
EN: His health condition limits his mobility.

ZH: 这部电影只限成年人观看。
EN: This movie is for adults only.

ZH: 由于资金限制，我们无法扩大业务规模。
EN: Due to financial constraints, we are unable to expand the business.

ZH: 网络游戏有时限，超过时间将自动断开连接。
EN: Online games have time limits and will disconnect automatically if exceeded.

ZH: 这个停车位每次使用的时间限制为两小时。
EN: The time limit for using this parking space is two hours each time.

ZH: 你的购物车中的物品数量已经超过了限制。
EN: The number of items in your shopping cart has exceeded the limit.

ZH: 您的信用卡已经达到了透支限制。
EN: Your credit card has reached its overdraft limit.

ZH: 请每人限制发言时间在两分钟内。
EN: Please limit your speaking time to two minutes per person.

ZH: 这个比赛的参加人数限制在五十人以内。
EN: The participation in this competition is limited to fifty people.

ZH: 快递服务的重量限制是5公斤。
EN: The weight limit for courier services is 5 kilograms.

ZH: 这种药物有年龄限制，只适用于成年人使用。
EN: This medication has an age restriction and is only suitable for adults.

ZH: 当今社会，我们被很多观念限制着。
EN: In today's society, we are limited by many beliefs.

ZH: 这个季节的蔬菜种类有限。
EN: The variety of vegetables available in this season is limited.

ZH: 面试时，你需要限制回答的长度。
EN: During the interview, you need to limit the length of your answers.

ZH: 该文件仅限内部员工访问。
EN: This document is accessible only to internal employees.

ZH: 请在限定区域内行驶。
EN: Please drive within the designated area.
